<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-185-234 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 536 133</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  April 1 1991 v8 n13 p24(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Firm unveils two graphics controllers. (Chips and TechnologiesInc.'s 82C453 and 82C480 graphics controllers) (Hardware) (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Chips and Technologies Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    CHPS.andO;Product:   Chips and Technologies 82C453 (Integrated circuit) (Productintroduction)Chips and Technologies 82C480 (Integrated circuit) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionComputer graphicsIntegrated circuits.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Aiming to boost high-end PCs' graphics performance, Chips and TechnologiesInc. last week unveiled two new controllers.andM;Chips and Technologies' new 82C453 Ultra VGA Controller doubles the speed ofgraphics applications such as Windows, said officials of the San Jose,Calif., company.andM;The 82C453 features a resolution of 1,024 by 768 pixels, and supports as manyas 256 colors.andM;Chips and Technologies also introduced a high-performance, single-chipcontroller compatible with IBM's 8514/A graphics adapter.andP;  The 82C480 givessystem designers access to &quot;workstation quality&quot; graphics displays, officialssaid.andP;  The new controller supports as many as 4M bytes of video RAM,resolutions as high as 1,280 by 1,024 pixels and 256 colors.andM;The 82C453 costs $30 each in volumes of 1,000; the 82C480 is available as asingle chip for $75 each in volumes of 1,000, or as a chip set that includesa video-support chip and a dual-clock chip for $95 each in volumes of 1,000.andO;Both are available now.andM;Chips and Technologies, which last year reported revenues of $300 million,can be reached at (408) 434-0600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>